Helped my 6 yr old color one of her dolls for Halloween and only used crayons and colored pencils . It wipes off and can be done over and over . This was the 5th time we drew on her . It took a few tries to figure out what looked best on her . Thinking about doing her cloth body with a coffee or tea dip . I hope the wax crayons on the cloth will add a little wax resist effect . Working on making her hair into the twists . Bought her from goodwill and having a blast watching my little artist creating her art . I love tiny human art !

Opened a package I got in the mail and this lil one crawled out . It was a lil smashed but moving well . Put it in a cup and got my 6 yr old to take it outside and let it go free . The spots on the front were just epic . Totally perfect giant decoy eye spots . I actually had to look really close a few times before I realized they were fake eyes . It looks like a cartoon ladybug or fake . It was sooo fast , I had a hard time taking a photo. I had to take about 10 pics to get 1 good shot . This lil one is a survivor. Ebay package with a bonus ladybug surprise !

Kids get home from school in 3hrs 45 mins, this mama will be updating one I figure out wTF . I know I we own a good sized Grogu. Going to go look at the other pics on the camera roll that my kids took … it’s a moms  life . Non stop fun here !

Man, the number of paranoid posts out there regarding vaccines is astonishing.  Anti-vax and paranoia have always existed, it's unfortunate that social media just seems to more easily bring these types together to feed in to a never-ending feedback loop of mis-information.  Just because someone else shares the same delusion doesn't make it more real, it just means you're not alone in your delusion.

PICKLED RED ONIONS
I add these to EVERYTHING!!! Don't knock it till you try it! 

INGREDIENTS
1 large red onion, thinly sliced
1 1/4 c. apple cider vinegar
1/2 c. water
3 tbsp. granulated sugar 
1 tbsp. kosher salt
Pinch of crushed red pepper flakes (optional)

DIRECTIONS
Place onion a large jar with a tight-fitting lid. 
In a medium saucepan over medium heat, bring vinegar, water, sugar, and salt to a boil. Stir until sugar and salt dissolve. Add in red pepper flakes, if using, then pour mixture over onions. 
Let cool to room temperature, then place lid on and refrigerate until ready to use, at least 2 hours. Onions will keep in refrigerator for up to 1 month.

(Image and recipe from https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a27245453/pickled-red-onions-recipe/ )
